# Trivy allowlist for HIGH/CRITICAL findings the gate cannot fix in P6.
# Each entry must reference a tracking note + revisit trigger.
#
# Format: one CVE per line. Comments allowed via leading `#`.

# ─── glob / minimatch transitive (jest 29 coverage path) ────────────────
# Forcing glob ^10.5 and minimatch ^9.0.7 breaks jest's coverage chain
# (test-exclude@6 → babel-plugin-istanbul) because those versions ship as
# ESM-only named exports while the consumer expects the legacy CommonJS
# function shape. Revisit when we bump to jest 30 (now GA) which uses
# updated test-exclude / babel-plugin-istanbul.
CVE-2025-64756    # glob 10.4.5
CVE-2026-26996    # minimatch 9.0.5
CVE-2026-27903    # minimatch 9.0.5
CVE-2026-27904    # minimatch 9.0.5

